[0.001, "o", "\u001b]2;claude -p 'What authentication method does this project use?'\u0007\u001b]1;claude\u0007"]
[26.704, "o", "This project uses **JWT (JSON Web Token) Bearer authentication** via the `jsonwebtoken` library.\r\n\r\nHere's how it works:\r\n\r\n- **Login** (`POST /api/auth/login`) — validates email/password against an in-memory store and returns a signed JWT with a 1-hour expiry (`src/routes/auth.ts:30-33`)\r\n- **Middleware** (`src/middleware/auth.ts`) — checks for a `Bearer` token in the `Authorization` header, verifies it using `jwt.verify` with `JWT_SECRET` from env, and attaches the decoded `{ id, role }` payload to the request\r\n- **Public routes** (`/api/auth/login`, `/api/auth/register`) are whitelisted and skip auth\r\n\r\nNotable caveats in the current implementation:\r\n- Passwords are stored **in plaintext** in memory (there's a TODO at `src/routes/auth.ts:17` to hash them)\r\n- The user store is **in-memory only** — no database\r\n- `JWT_SECRET` is expected from `process.env` with no fallback\r\n"]
